WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.420 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.420 --> 00:00:09.680 align:middle line:90%


00:00:09.680 --> 00:00:13.905 align:middle line:84%
>> I was a corporate lawyer
working 60 to 80-hour weeks

00:00:13.905 --> 00:00:14.705 align:middle line:90%
for many years.

00:00:14.705 --> 00:00:17.800 align:middle line:90%


00:00:17.800 --> 00:00:20.930 align:middle line:10%
I had spent the better
part of my life chasing

00:00:20.930 --> 00:00:24.680 align:middle line:10%
that American dream without ever
really thinking about what I

00:00:24.680 --> 00:00:26.510 align:middle line:10%
wanted to do with my life.

00:00:26.510 --> 00:00:30.370 align:middle line:90%


00:00:30.370 --> 00:00:32.369 align:middle line:10%
And I wasn't taking care
of myself physically.

00:00:32.369 --> 00:00:33.990 align:middle line:10%
I'd become a junk food addict.

00:00:33.990 --> 00:00:36.030 align:middle line:10%
I was not exercising at all.

00:00:36.030 --> 00:00:38.730 align:middle line:10%
I was 50 pounds overweight,
and I have a history

00:00:38.730 --> 00:00:40.500 align:middle line:10%
of addiction and alcoholism.

00:00:40.500 --> 00:00:43.820 align:middle line:90%


00:00:43.820 --> 00:00:46.920 align:middle line:10%
I was also very depressed.

00:00:46.920 --> 00:00:48.920 align:middle line:10%
And it all caught
up to me shortly

00:00:48.920 --> 00:00:52.120 align:middle line:10%
before my 40th birthday.

00:00:52.120 --> 00:00:54.100 align:middle line:10%
Late one evening as
I was making my way

00:00:54.100 --> 00:00:58.470 align:middle line:10%
up a simple flight of stairs,
I literally had to pause.

00:00:58.470 --> 00:00:59.520 align:middle line:10%
I was so winded.

00:00:59.520 --> 00:01:02.760 align:middle line:10%
I had tightness in my chest
and shortness of breath

00:01:02.760 --> 00:01:06.360 align:middle line:10%
and sweat on my brow and
really, like, fear in my heart

00:01:06.360 --> 00:01:09.745 align:middle line:10%
that I was on the precipice
of having a heart incident.

00:01:09.745 --> 00:01:13.850 align:middle line:90%


00:01:13.850 --> 00:01:15.350 align:middle line:10%
My whole life, my
mother would say,

00:01:15.350 --> 00:01:17.320 align:middle line:10%
you got to watch what
you eat and be careful,

00:01:17.320 --> 00:01:20.510 align:middle line:10%
but it all became very crystal
clear to me in that moment,

00:01:20.510 --> 00:01:23.510 align:middle line:10%
not only that I needed to
change how I was living,

00:01:23.510 --> 00:01:26.090 align:middle line:10%
how I was behaving,
how I was prioritizing

00:01:26.090 --> 00:01:29.180 align:middle line:10%
my time and my energy,
but also that I

00:01:29.180 --> 00:01:30.490 align:middle line:10%
wanted to make that change.

00:01:30.490 --> 00:01:33.380 align:middle line:84%
I had a willingness to
take a leap of faith

00:01:33.380 --> 00:01:34.937 align:middle line:90%
and try something different.

00:01:34.937 --> 00:01:37.800 align:middle line:90%


00:01:37.800 --> 00:01:40.680 align:middle line:84%
The first thing that I did was
a seven-day fruit and vegetable

00:01:40.680 --> 00:01:44.010 align:middle line:84%
juice cleanse, which
was crazy at the time.

00:01:44.010 --> 00:01:47.625 align:middle line:84%
It was so out of left field from
anything I'd ever experienced.

00:01:47.625 --> 00:01:49.500 align:middle line:84%
I'd never gone a single
day in my entire life

00:01:49.500 --> 00:01:51.090 align:middle line:90%
without eating solid food.

00:01:51.090 --> 00:01:56.430 align:middle line:84%
But I knew that that was
something that would kind

00:01:56.430 --> 00:01:58.590 align:middle line:90%
of shock me out of my habits.

00:01:58.590 --> 00:02:01.810 align:middle line:84%
It didn't have to do with
detoxing or any of that.

00:02:01.810 --> 00:02:05.400 align:middle line:84%
I just needed to do something
extreme to kind of reframe

00:02:05.400 --> 00:02:07.590 align:middle line:84%
my relationship with food,
and it was very effective

00:02:07.590 --> 00:02:08.880 align:middle line:90%
in that regard.

00:02:08.880 --> 00:02:10.500 align:middle line:84%
Over that seven-day
period, I can

00:02:10.500 --> 00:02:15.360 align:middle line:84%
remember lying on the couch,
being listless and sweating

00:02:15.360 --> 00:02:17.970 align:middle line:84%
and thinking, how am I going
to make it through the day?

00:02:17.970 --> 00:02:19.860 align:middle line:84%
But the remarkable
thing is that at the end

00:02:19.860 --> 00:02:22.740 align:middle line:84%
of that one-week week period,
I felt completely revitalized.

00:02:22.740 --> 00:02:26.767 align:middle line:84%
I had a resurgence of vitality
and energy and mental clarity

00:02:26.767 --> 00:02:28.975 align:middle line:84%
that I hadn't experienced
since I was a young person.

00:02:28.975 --> 00:02:32.400 align:middle line:90%


00:02:32.400 --> 00:02:35.078 align:middle line:84%
And I had all this
energy for the first time

00:02:35.078 --> 00:02:36.370 align:middle line:90%
in as long as I could remember.

00:02:36.370 --> 00:02:40.530 align:middle line:84%
So the impulse to actually
move myself physically

00:02:40.530 --> 00:02:42.090 align:middle line:84%
occurred to me,
which is something

00:02:42.090 --> 00:02:44.790 align:middle line:90%
I hadn't felt in a while also.

00:02:44.790 --> 00:02:48.240 align:middle line:84%
And so I started exercising
again, first very casually.

00:02:48.240 --> 00:02:51.370 align:middle line:84%
But I realized very quickly
that I enjoyed that,

00:02:51.370 --> 00:02:54.222 align:middle line:84%
and it was a big part of
what I was about as a child

00:02:54.222 --> 00:02:55.680 align:middle line:84%
and something that
I love very much

00:02:55.680 --> 00:02:57.370 align:middle line:84%
and had really
lost touch with it.

00:02:57.370 --> 00:03:01.800 align:middle line:84%
But I think what it evolved
into was this pursuit of trying

00:03:01.800 --> 00:03:04.980 align:middle line:90%
to unlock hidden potential.

00:03:04.980 --> 00:03:07.230 align:middle line:10%
In a very short period
of time after changing

00:03:07.230 --> 00:03:11.410 align:middle line:10%
my relationship with food, I
had completely transformed.

00:03:11.410 --> 00:03:12.930 align:middle line:10%
I lost 50 pounds.

00:03:12.930 --> 00:03:13.990 align:middle line:10%
I looked different.

00:03:13.990 --> 00:03:14.820 align:middle line:10%
I felt different.

00:03:14.820 --> 00:03:18.000 align:middle line:10%
It was quite radical, and
yet the changes that I made

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:19.620 align:middle line:10%
were relatively simple.

00:03:19.620 --> 00:03:21.420 align:middle line:84%
And the thought
occurred to me, if I

00:03:21.420 --> 00:03:24.210 align:middle line:84%
could change this
drastically, this dramatically

00:03:24.210 --> 00:03:26.310 align:middle line:84%
in such a short
period of time, what

00:03:26.310 --> 00:03:29.520 align:middle line:84%
are the other areas of my life
that I'm overlooking where I'm

00:03:29.520 --> 00:03:32.670 align:middle line:84%
sitting on top of
mountains of potential

00:03:32.670 --> 00:03:35.190 align:middle line:84%
that I'm just not
consciously aware of?

00:03:35.190 --> 00:03:38.160 align:middle line:84%
And that's what lured me
into the world of triathlon

00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:41.280 align:middle line:84%
initially and ultimately into
ultra endurance athletics

00:03:41.280 --> 00:03:42.760 align:middle line:84%
because I was a
swimmer in college,

00:03:42.760 --> 00:03:45.360 align:middle line:84%
so I had that
background, and I knew

00:03:45.360 --> 00:03:47.230 align:middle line:90%
how to train and push myself.

00:03:47.230 --> 00:03:50.070 align:middle line:84%
And as I sort of got
fitter and more invested

00:03:50.070 --> 00:03:52.260 align:middle line:84%
in this food adventure
that I was on,

00:03:52.260 --> 00:03:54.840 align:middle line:84%
I started getting more
interested in fitness

00:03:54.840 --> 00:03:55.980 align:middle line:90%
in general.

00:03:55.980 --> 00:03:59.100 align:middle line:84%
And I had unfinished business
as a competitive swimmer,

00:03:59.100 --> 00:04:02.710 align:middle line:84%
and I never felt like I achieved
my potential as an athlete.

00:04:02.710 --> 00:04:05.410 align:middle line:84%
And so here I was
at 40, 41 years old

00:04:05.410 --> 00:04:09.270 align:middle line:84%
having this kind of renaissance
experience and thinking, well,

00:04:09.270 --> 00:04:11.490 align:middle line:84%
maybe I can be
competitive again.

00:04:11.490 --> 00:04:12.480 align:middle line:90%
Let's give this a go.

00:04:12.480 --> 00:04:15.210 align:middle line:84%
And I read this article about
this crazy race, Ultraman,

00:04:15.210 --> 00:04:18.029 align:middle line:84%
which is a double Ironman
distance triathlon that

00:04:18.029 --> 00:04:20.430 align:middle line:84%
circumnavigates the entire
big island of Hawaii

00:04:20.430 --> 00:04:21.690 align:middle line:90%
over three days.

00:04:21.690 --> 00:04:23.130 align:middle line:90%
It's 320 miles.

00:04:23.130 --> 00:04:25.450 align:middle line:90%
It's absolutely bananas.

00:04:25.450 --> 00:04:28.140 align:middle line:84%
It was like a light switch went
off in my mind and I thought,

00:04:28.140 --> 00:04:29.430 align:middle line:90%
that's the race for me.

00:04:29.430 --> 00:04:30.610 align:middle line:90%
It made no sense.

00:04:30.610 --> 00:04:32.440 align:middle line:90%
It's not logical at all.

00:04:32.440 --> 00:04:38.280 align:middle line:84%
It was more like this bizarre
calling that I felt. Like,

00:04:38.280 --> 00:04:39.600 align:middle line:90%
it just felt right.

00:04:39.600 --> 00:04:41.640 align:middle line:84%
I was like, that's
what I'm doing,

00:04:41.640 --> 00:04:44.250 align:middle line:84%
and I could see
myself, in my mind,

00:04:44.250 --> 00:04:45.780 align:middle line:90%
lining up at the start line.

00:04:45.780 --> 00:04:47.070 align:middle line:90%
I knew it was going to happen.

00:04:47.070 --> 00:04:49.530 align:middle line:84%
It was like a foregone
conclusion despite the fact

00:04:49.530 --> 00:04:52.000 align:middle line:84%
that it made no
sense whatsoever.

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:55.110 align:middle line:84%
And I had one goal, and
that goal was don't die.

00:04:55.110 --> 00:05:18.080 align:middle line:90%


00:05:18.080 --> 00:05:22.880 align:middle line:84%
>> We don't set goals or
define success based on our own

00:05:22.880 --> 00:05:26.870 align:middle line:84%
self-identity but based on
what I call the culturescape.

00:05:26.870 --> 00:05:30.560 align:middle line:84%
The culturescape is that
tangled web of rituals, habits,

00:05:30.560 --> 00:05:33.660 align:middle line:84%
beliefs, mythologies,
practices that our culture,

00:05:33.660 --> 00:05:36.610 align:middle line:84%
our religions, our
countries, through schooling,

00:05:36.610 --> 00:05:38.360 align:middle line:84%
through education,
through media,

00:05:38.360 --> 00:05:41.900 align:middle line:84%
infuse us in terms of
what is the right way

00:05:41.900 --> 00:05:43.473 align:middle line:90%
to function in the world.

00:05:43.473 --> 00:05:45.140 align:middle line:84%
Now, post-World War
II, the culturescape

00:05:45.140 --> 00:05:48.330 align:middle line:84%
was really about rebuilding,
about being safe.

00:05:48.330 --> 00:05:50.840 align:middle line:84%
But in today's
world, we are safe.

00:05:50.840 --> 00:05:53.360 align:middle line:84%
And so in today's world,
the millennial generation,

00:05:53.360 --> 00:05:56.930 align:middle line:84%
the big thing that they want
to pursue is self-discovery,

00:05:56.930 --> 00:05:58.230 align:middle line:90%
is creation.

00:05:58.230 --> 00:06:01.820 align:middle line:84%
The problem is, the culturescape
keeps engulfing us and telling

00:06:01.820 --> 00:06:03.470 align:middle line:84%
us that we need
a college degree,

00:06:03.470 --> 00:06:06.810 align:middle line:84%
we need to get a good career,
we need to work the 9:00 to 5:00

00:06:06.810 --> 00:06:08.460 align:middle line:84%
so we can make partner
in that law firm

00:06:08.460 --> 00:06:11.990 align:middle line:84%
so we can have 2.5 cars in the
garage, a wife, and two kids

00:06:11.990 --> 00:06:14.710 align:middle line:84%
so that someday when we are 60,
we can finally retire and see

00:06:14.710 --> 00:06:15.510 align:middle line:90%
the world.

00:06:15.510 --> 00:06:18.410 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is, those
rules don't apply anymore.

00:06:18.410 --> 00:06:20.790 align:middle line:84%
The culturescape was
designed to keep us safe.

00:06:20.790 --> 00:06:23.810 align:middle line:84%
But it was never designed
to keep us happy.

00:06:23.810 --> 00:06:26.360 align:middle line:10%
>> We were taught in the
'80s and the '90s, which is

00:06:26.360 --> 00:06:30.560 align:middle line:10%
basically consumerism, which
was lean on other things,

00:06:30.560 --> 00:06:34.170 align:middle line:10%
which was attain power,
money, wealth, status,

00:06:34.170 --> 00:06:35.570 align:middle line:10%
and you'll feel good--

00:06:35.570 --> 00:06:37.640 align:middle line:10%
but you have an
entire economy now

00:06:37.640 --> 00:06:40.340 align:middle line:10%
that's chugged along pretty
well for decade after decade

00:06:40.340 --> 00:06:41.420 align:middle line:10%
after decade.

00:06:41.420 --> 00:06:43.920 align:middle line:84%
You've got a lot of comfort,
especially in the United States

00:06:43.920 --> 00:06:45.200 align:middle line:90%
and the Western worlds now.

00:06:45.200 --> 00:06:46.830 align:middle line:84%
We haven't solved
all the problems.

00:06:46.830 --> 00:06:50.690 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of still people
living in just abject poverty.

00:06:50.690 --> 00:06:53.260 align:middle line:84%
But as more and more of the
world reaches middle class,

00:06:53.260 --> 00:06:55.760 align:middle line:84%
then they fought to get there,
then they kind of look around

00:06:55.760 --> 00:06:58.070 align:middle line:90%
go, is this it?

00:06:58.070 --> 00:07:00.290 align:middle line:90%
I still don't feel good.

00:07:00.290 --> 00:07:02.640 align:middle line:84%
I still feel like I
did when I was broke.

00:07:02.640 --> 00:07:05.870 align:middle line:84%
I still feel like I did
when I was struggling.

00:07:05.870 --> 00:07:09.200 align:middle line:84%
And people are having trouble
connecting with themselves.

00:07:09.200 --> 00:07:12.980 align:middle line:84%
>> As Henry David Thoreau said
so eloquently, I truly believe,

00:07:12.980 --> 00:07:15.830 align:middle line:84%
"the mass of men lead lives
of quiet desperation,"

00:07:15.830 --> 00:07:19.450 align:middle line:84%
and "what is considered
resignation is confirmed

00:07:19.450 --> 00:07:20.725 align:middle line:90%
desperation."

00:07:20.725 --> 00:07:22.310 align:middle line:90%
I think it was true in his time.

00:07:22.310 --> 00:07:24.530 align:middle line:84%
I think it's probably
more true now.

00:07:24.530 --> 00:07:30.050 align:middle line:10%
There are so many people who are
dissatisfied with their lives.

00:07:30.050 --> 00:07:33.440 align:middle line:84%
They're living their lives
reactively, compulsively,

00:07:33.440 --> 00:07:35.990 align:middle line:84%
and not mindfully
or consciously.

00:07:35.990 --> 00:07:37.940 align:middle line:84%
And it's really not
even their own fault.

00:07:37.940 --> 00:07:40.820 align:middle line:84%
We are living all in
this system that's

00:07:40.820 --> 00:07:43.400 align:middle line:84%
set up to drive us
onto career paths

00:07:43.400 --> 00:07:46.010 align:middle line:84%
that we're not consciously
choosing for ourselves

00:07:46.010 --> 00:07:50.537 align:middle line:84%
or that are out of alignment
with who we truly are.

00:07:50.537 --> 00:07:52.370 align:middle line:84%
>> But we take goals
that belong to society.

00:07:52.370 --> 00:07:54.078 align:middle line:84%
We take goals that
belong to our parents.

00:07:54.078 --> 00:07:56.210 align:middle line:10%
We take goals that
we think and justify

00:07:56.210 --> 00:07:59.913 align:middle line:10%
and rationalize that we
need in order to be happy.

00:07:59.913 --> 00:08:01.580 align:middle line:84%
And I found myself
reaching the pinnacle

00:08:01.580 --> 00:08:04.280 align:middle line:84%
of these mountains, the mountain
being a metaphor for life.

00:08:04.280 --> 00:08:06.140 align:middle line:84%
So I'd reached this
pinnacle, and I'd

00:08:06.140 --> 00:08:09.270 align:middle line:84%
stand on the top this mountain
and look around and go,

00:08:09.270 --> 00:08:10.990 align:middle line:84%
I thought I would
feel different.

00:08:10.990 --> 00:08:13.748 align:middle line:84%
I thought I'd be happy or I
thought I'd be more content.

00:08:13.748 --> 00:08:15.290 align:middle line:84%
And then I'd look
across the horizon.

00:08:15.290 --> 00:08:16.998 align:middle line:84%
I'd see another mountain
in the distance.

00:08:16.998 --> 00:08:20.280 align:middle line:84%
I'd go, ah, here's the problem,
I climbed the wrong mountain.

00:08:20.280 --> 00:08:22.320 align:middle line:84%
Now, when I climb that
mountain in the distance,

00:08:22.320 --> 00:08:23.243 align:middle line:90%
then I'll be happy.

00:08:23.243 --> 00:08:24.910 align:middle line:84%
And I would come down
off this, mountain

00:08:24.910 --> 00:08:26.225 align:middle line:90%
and I'd cross the valley.

00:08:26.225 --> 00:08:28.350 align:middle line:84%
And again, this valley
represented years of my life

00:08:28.350 --> 00:08:29.808 align:middle line:90%
in some cases.

00:08:29.808 --> 00:08:31.350 align:middle line:84%
And I'd climb another
mountain, which

00:08:31.350 --> 00:08:33.720 align:middle line:84%
represented another business,
another financial goal,

00:08:33.720 --> 00:08:36.000 align:middle line:84%
another material goal, or
even a relationship goal.

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:39.690 align:middle line:84%
I'd get to the top of that, and
the same pattern followed me.

00:08:39.690 --> 00:08:42.570 align:middle line:84%
Why don't I just
stop and ask myself,

00:08:42.570 --> 00:08:46.620 align:middle line:84%
why, when I achieve
something, is it not enough?

00:08:46.620 --> 00:08:50.020 align:middle line:90%


00:08:50.020 --> 00:08:52.690 align:middle line:84%
>> Hunter S. Thompson,
the American writer,

00:08:52.690 --> 00:08:55.830 align:middle line:84%
in 1953 was asked to write
a letter to a friend.

00:08:55.830 --> 00:08:57.580 align:middle line:84%
His friend was
asking for advice.

00:08:57.580 --> 00:09:00.340 align:middle line:84%
Hunter says, the danger
with goal setting

00:09:00.340 --> 00:09:03.910 align:middle line:84%
is very often the goals that
you set are not your goals.

00:09:03.910 --> 00:09:05.950 align:middle line:84%
They are the
culturescape's definition

00:09:05.950 --> 00:09:09.340 align:middle line:84%
of how you are meant to
be safe in the world.

00:09:09.340 --> 00:09:12.280 align:middle line:84%
But that is one of the
sure response to misery,

00:09:12.280 --> 00:09:14.240 align:middle line:84%
to waking up one day
at the age of 40 going,

00:09:14.240 --> 00:09:16.120 align:middle line:84%
what the hell
happened to my life?

00:09:16.120 --> 00:09:20.530 align:middle line:84%
And so we always
have to question.

00:09:20.530 --> 00:09:23.560 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the keys to setting
goals that are really going

00:09:23.560 --> 00:09:26.840 align:middle line:84%
to be incredible for you
is, do they excite you?

00:09:26.840 --> 00:09:29.110 align:middle line:84%
If you look at them on
that piece of paper,

00:09:29.110 --> 00:09:30.580 align:middle line:90%
does it bring you to life?

00:09:30.580 --> 00:09:31.660 align:middle line:90%
Does it bring you joy?

00:09:31.660 --> 00:09:35.253 align:middle line:84%
Does it make you have
those little mix of fear

00:09:35.253 --> 00:09:36.670 align:middle line:84%
and anticipation,
and you're like,

00:09:36.670 --> 00:09:38.650 align:middle line:84%
you can't wait to
dive into them?

00:09:38.650 --> 00:09:42.020 align:middle line:84%
If not, something's
probably wrong.

00:09:42.020 --> 00:09:46.150 align:middle line:84%
So if we're setting goals out
of fear or a place of pain,

00:09:46.150 --> 00:09:47.980 align:middle line:90%
that's not necessarily bad.

00:09:47.980 --> 00:09:50.050 align:middle line:84%
We can either change
our lives from a space

00:09:50.050 --> 00:09:51.890 align:middle line:90%
of inspiration or desperation.

00:09:51.890 --> 00:09:55.690 align:middle line:84%
And so many of us hit a pain
point where we're suffering,

00:09:55.690 --> 00:09:56.620 align:middle line:90%
we're depressed.

00:09:56.620 --> 00:09:58.990 align:middle line:84%
We have hit this
place in our lives,

00:09:58.990 --> 00:10:01.270 align:middle line:84%
whether it's emotionally
in a relationship,

00:10:01.270 --> 00:10:04.670 align:middle line:84%
financially in our careers,
where something is not working.

00:10:04.670 --> 00:10:06.760 align:middle line:84%
And we find ourselves
feeling like we're beating

00:10:06.760 --> 00:10:08.080 align:middle line:90%
our head against a wall.

00:10:08.080 --> 00:10:11.230 align:middle line:84%
If you're setting a goal out of
I can't take this pain anymore,

00:10:11.230 --> 00:10:13.000 align:middle line:84%
that's not necessarily
bad because we

00:10:13.000 --> 00:10:14.840 align:middle line:90%
have to start where we are.

00:10:14.840 --> 00:10:17.020 align:middle line:84%
But when you're
looking at your goals,

00:10:17.020 --> 00:10:19.880 align:middle line:84%
if they don't make you
want to jump out of bed,

00:10:19.880 --> 00:10:22.540 align:middle line:84%
stay up all night,
just get so fired up

00:10:22.540 --> 00:10:25.750 align:middle line:84%
about figuring out how to
bring them into the world,

00:10:25.750 --> 00:10:28.360 align:middle line:84%
then I think it's time
for some re-evaluation.

00:10:28.360 --> 00:10:31.120 align:middle line:84%
>> I think a lot of people
set goals based on what

00:10:31.120 --> 00:10:33.710 align:middle line:84%
their family or their
peers want them to do.

00:10:33.710 --> 00:10:36.900 align:middle line:84%
And that's good if it's
also what you want to do.

00:10:36.900 --> 00:10:38.760 align:middle line:84%
But a lot of times,
people chase things

00:10:38.760 --> 00:10:40.510 align:middle line:84%
that they don't fully
love, and so they're

00:10:40.510 --> 00:10:41.655 align:middle line:90%
living someone else's life.

00:10:41.655 --> 00:10:43.030 align:middle line:84%
So I think you
got to figure out,

00:10:43.030 --> 00:10:45.447 align:middle line:84%
what are the things that brings
you the most joy, the most

00:10:45.447 --> 00:10:47.470 align:middle line:90%
passion, the most meaning?

00:10:47.470 --> 00:10:51.760 align:middle line:84%
>> For me, it was simple
as I just love jumping

00:10:51.760 --> 00:10:55.180 align:middle line:84%
into a swimming pool in the
morning or I love the feeling

00:10:55.180 --> 00:11:00.190 align:middle line:84%
of how the sun hits my shoulder
on a trail run at dawn.

00:11:00.190 --> 00:11:04.240 align:middle line:84%
Those were things I wanted
to have more of in my life--

00:11:04.240 --> 00:11:09.100 align:middle line:84%
very simple, basic, ultimately
quite primal instincts.

00:11:09.100 --> 00:11:16.150 align:middle line:90%


00:11:16.150 --> 00:11:18.190 align:middle line:84%
2008 was my first
Ultraman, and I

00:11:18.190 --> 00:11:21.490 align:middle line:84%
was very conservative in my
approach and very conscious

00:11:21.490 --> 00:11:23.710 align:middle line:84%
that I was a newcomer
in this sport.

00:11:23.710 --> 00:11:26.420 align:middle line:84%
But I ended up being the
second fastest American.

00:11:26.420 --> 00:11:30.190 align:middle line:84%
I think I was 11th
overall that year,

00:11:30.190 --> 00:11:32.890 align:middle line:84%
far exceeding my expectations
and the expectations

00:11:32.890 --> 00:11:34.700 align:middle line:84%
of everyone else
involved in the event.

00:11:34.700 --> 00:11:37.240 align:middle line:84%
So I thought, what would happen
if I trained a whole year

00:11:37.240 --> 00:11:40.861 align:middle line:84%
and went back to that race fully
prepared with some experience?

00:11:40.861 --> 00:11:46.520 align:middle line:90%


00:11:46.520 --> 00:11:49.370 align:middle line:90%
So in 2009, that's what I did.

00:11:49.370 --> 00:11:52.130 align:middle line:10%
I was the fastest American that
year and was sixth overall.

00:11:52.130 --> 00:11:55.070 align:middle line:90%


00:11:55.070 --> 00:11:57.970 align:middle line:84%
Ultraman was really driven
by this question, this quest

00:11:57.970 --> 00:12:00.490 align:middle line:84%
that I was on, which
was to determine

00:12:00.490 --> 00:12:02.650 align:middle line:84%
the outer limits
of my capabilities,

00:12:02.650 --> 00:12:05.600 align:middle line:84%
physically, mentally,
emotionally, and spiritually.

00:12:05.600 --> 00:12:08.660 align:middle line:84%
What am I truly capable of if
I really put it on the line

00:12:08.660 --> 00:12:09.460 align:middle line:90%
and test myself?

00:12:09.460 --> 00:12:23.970 align:middle line:90%


00:12:23.970 --> 00:12:26.280 align:middle line:84%
>> When I was a kid, I was
watching sports with my dad

00:12:26.280 --> 00:12:28.590 align:middle line:84%
on the couch, and we'd see
these all-Americans who were

00:12:28.590 --> 00:12:30.880 align:middle line:84%
the greatest in the
country, and I said, well,

00:12:30.880 --> 00:12:31.922 align:middle line:90%
that's what I want to be.

00:12:31.922 --> 00:12:34.833 align:middle line:84%
I want to be one of the
greatest in the country.

00:12:34.833 --> 00:12:36.250 align:middle line:84%
That was the dream,
and I actually

00:12:36.250 --> 00:12:41.520 align:middle line:84%
achieved that dream of being
all-American in two sports.

00:12:41.520 --> 00:12:44.500 align:middle line:84%
But then, ultimately, it's to
go get paid to do what you love,

00:12:44.500 --> 00:12:47.270 align:middle line:84%
and that was to be a
professional football player.

00:12:47.270 --> 00:12:49.410 align:middle line:84%
I did it for a little
bit until I got injured.

00:12:49.410 --> 00:12:52.840 align:middle line:84%
I broke my wrist diving into
a wall playing arena football

00:12:52.840 --> 00:12:53.830 align:middle line:90%
and snapped my wrist.

00:12:53.830 --> 00:12:57.070 align:middle line:90%


00:12:57.070 --> 00:12:58.570 align:middle line:84%
And so for the next
year and a half,

00:12:58.570 --> 00:13:01.540 align:middle line:84%
I was on my sister's couch,
six months in a full arm cast.

00:13:01.540 --> 00:13:04.410 align:middle line:90%


00:13:04.410 --> 00:13:06.250 align:middle line:84%
I didn't have a college
degree at the time.

00:13:06.250 --> 00:13:08.620 align:middle line:84%
I didn't really go to
school to learn anything

00:13:08.620 --> 00:13:10.233 align:middle line:90%
except for to play sports.

00:13:10.233 --> 00:13:11.650 align:middle line:84%
So I didn't have
any other skills.

00:13:11.650 --> 00:13:15.700 align:middle line:84%
This was in the height of the
economic challenge in the US

00:13:15.700 --> 00:13:19.450 align:middle line:84%
in 2008, 2009, where people with
degrees weren't getting jobs.

00:13:19.450 --> 00:13:22.920 align:middle line:90%


00:13:22.920 --> 00:13:25.000 align:middle line:84%
I really didn't know
what to do next.

00:13:25.000 --> 00:13:28.080 align:middle line:84%
My whole identity was wrapped
around in being an athlete,

00:13:28.080 --> 00:13:31.798 align:middle line:84%
and now I couldn't
do that anymore.

00:13:31.798 --> 00:13:33.840 align:middle line:84%
Your friends no longer
want to hang out with you.

00:13:33.840 --> 00:13:35.173 align:middle line:90%
You're not getting acknowledged.

00:13:35.173 --> 00:13:40.690 align:middle line:84%
So for me, it was extremely
depressing for many months.

00:13:40.690 --> 00:13:43.630 align:middle line:84%
It's really challenging when you
lose your identity, especially

00:13:43.630 --> 00:13:44.440 align:middle line:90%
as an athlete.

00:13:44.440 --> 00:13:45.940 align:middle line:84%
This is the way
you've been praised.

00:13:45.940 --> 00:13:48.315 align:middle line:84%
This is the way you've been
acknowledged your entire life

00:13:48.315 --> 00:13:51.400 align:middle line:84%
as being this good or great
athlete, known for this one

00:13:51.400 --> 00:13:52.970 align:middle line:90%
thing that you can do.

00:13:52.970 --> 00:13:55.330 align:middle line:10%
So when you can no
longer do the one thing

00:13:55.330 --> 00:13:57.880 align:middle line:10%
that everyone praises you
and acknowledges you for,

00:13:57.880 --> 00:14:00.870 align:middle line:10%
then you don't get
acknowledgment anymore.

00:14:00.870 --> 00:14:03.220 align:middle line:84%
So I'm just thinking,
well, who am I?

00:14:03.220 --> 00:14:04.020 align:middle line:90%
Why am I here?

00:14:04.020 --> 00:14:04.990 align:middle line:90%
What's my purpose?

00:14:04.990 --> 00:14:08.280 align:middle line:84%
And that's the challenge is
rediscovering and reinventing

00:14:08.280 --> 00:14:10.275 align:middle line:90%
my purpose once I lost my dream.

00:14:10.275 --> 00:14:12.900 align:middle line:84%
So I had to learn about just how
to become a better human being

00:14:12.900 --> 00:14:17.160 align:middle line:84%
and not rely on my
athletic abilities.

00:14:17.160 --> 00:14:19.360 align:middle line:84%
In my first half
my life, I really

00:14:19.360 --> 00:14:22.880 align:middle line:84%
was committed to my dreams in
order to prove people wrong.

00:14:22.880 --> 00:14:25.270 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to be a professional
athlete because people

00:14:25.270 --> 00:14:28.990 align:middle line:84%
said I couldn't do it, because
kids picked on me, because I

00:14:28.990 --> 00:14:31.375 align:middle line:84%
was picked last on
the dodgeball game,

00:14:31.375 --> 00:14:33.250 align:middle line:84%
because I didn't have
many friends growing up

00:14:33.250 --> 00:14:34.640 align:middle line:90%
in elementary school.

00:14:34.640 --> 00:14:36.820 align:middle line:84%
So I said, I'm going
to do this to prove

00:14:36.820 --> 00:14:44.355 align:middle line:84%
everyone wrong about me and to
prove to them how good I am.

00:14:44.355 --> 00:14:45.730 align:middle line:84%
So for the first
half of my life,

00:14:45.730 --> 00:14:50.560 align:middle line:84%
I was driven by a negative
fuel around this goal,

00:14:50.560 --> 00:14:53.470 align:middle line:84%
and that negative
drive was so powerful

00:14:53.470 --> 00:14:54.610 align:middle line:90%
that it allowed me to--

00:14:54.610 --> 00:14:56.700 align:middle line:90%
it helped me to achieve my goal.

00:14:56.700 --> 00:14:57.690 align:middle line:90%
I was so focused.

00:14:57.690 --> 00:14:59.340 align:middle line:90%
I knew exactly what I wanted.

00:14:59.340 --> 00:15:01.530 align:middle line:84%
But the energy behind
it was negative.

00:15:01.530 --> 00:15:05.700 align:middle line:84%
It was to prove five people
wrong who doubted me.

00:15:05.700 --> 00:15:07.690 align:middle line:84%
And so when I
achieved my goal, I

00:15:07.690 --> 00:15:09.730 align:middle line:84%
remember feeling
so empty inside.

00:15:09.730 --> 00:15:11.560 align:middle line:90%
It's like, OK, I had the goal.

00:15:11.560 --> 00:15:12.460 align:middle line:90%
I had the structure.

00:15:12.460 --> 00:15:14.710 align:middle line:84%
I had the game plan, the
daily actions, all the things

00:15:14.710 --> 00:15:16.930 align:middle line:90%
we talk about, and it happened.

00:15:16.930 --> 00:15:18.220 align:middle line:90%
Why am I still not happy?

00:15:18.220 --> 00:15:19.330 align:middle line:90%
Why am I unfulfilled?

00:15:19.330 --> 00:15:24.160 align:middle line:84%
Why was I actually angrier after
I achieved it than ever before?

00:15:24.160 --> 00:15:27.050 align:middle line:84%
I was so disciplined
for 15 years of my life,

00:15:27.050 --> 00:15:30.400 align:middle line:84%
and now I got exactly what I
wanted, and I wasn't happy.

00:15:30.400 --> 00:15:32.810 align:middle line:84%
And I reflected on this and
said, well, maybe my goal

00:15:32.810 --> 00:15:33.890 align:middle line:90%
is just not big enough.

00:15:33.890 --> 00:15:35.640 align:middle line:84%
I need to go after
a bigger goal.

00:15:35.640 --> 00:15:38.740 align:middle line:84%
And so I kept going after these
unrealistic goals in business

00:15:38.740 --> 00:15:41.950 align:middle line:84%
and life, but it was all
based on this negative fuel

00:15:41.950 --> 00:15:43.210 align:middle line:90%
of proving people wrong.

00:15:43.210 --> 00:15:45.460 align:middle line:84%
>> So often when someone
sets out to achieve something

00:15:45.460 --> 00:15:47.793 align:middle line:84%
significant that
they've set out--

00:15:47.793 --> 00:15:49.960 align:middle line:84%
and even though they have
this inkling in their soul

00:15:49.960 --> 00:15:53.200 align:middle line:84%
that this is not me
anymore, this this

00:15:53.200 --> 00:15:55.190 align:middle line:90%
is not aligned to who I am--

00:15:55.190 --> 00:15:57.190 align:middle line:84%
they've set it out as an
intention to the world,

00:15:57.190 --> 00:15:58.240 align:middle line:90%
so they can't let it go.

00:15:58.240 --> 00:16:00.340 align:middle line:84%
So we just stubbornly
move towards the edge

00:16:00.340 --> 00:16:03.490 align:middle line:84%
of the cliff, which represents
an emotional crisis,

00:16:03.490 --> 00:16:06.850 align:middle line:84%
a breakdown, a slap in the face,
whatever you want to call it.

00:16:06.850 --> 00:16:21.920 align:middle line:90%


00:16:21.920 --> 00:16:24.440 align:middle line:84%
The question I always ask is,
who are you seeking validation

00:16:24.440 --> 00:16:25.590 align:middle line:90%
from?

00:16:25.590 --> 00:16:27.470 align:middle line:84%
And if you sit
with that question

00:16:27.470 --> 00:16:30.500 align:middle line:84%
and honestly answer that,
truthfully look in the mirror

00:16:30.500 --> 00:16:33.070 align:middle line:84%
and really answer that question
and sit with that question,

00:16:33.070 --> 00:16:35.720 align:middle line:84%
I have never found a human being
that's not seeking validation

00:16:35.720 --> 00:16:37.410 align:middle line:90%
from somebody else.

00:16:37.410 --> 00:16:39.140 align:middle line:84%
And typically, it's
those closest to us.

00:16:39.140 --> 00:16:41.120 align:middle line:84%
So if we think about
humans, a lot of humans

00:16:41.120 --> 00:16:43.010 align:middle line:84%
care deeply what
other people think.

00:16:43.010 --> 00:16:46.580 align:middle line:84%
You bring that back to your own
home, your family, your mother,

00:16:46.580 --> 00:16:50.670 align:middle line:84%
your father, typically, you
can multiply that by 1,000.

00:16:50.670 --> 00:16:53.170 align:middle line:84%
And when you look
at that and then

00:16:53.170 --> 00:16:54.920 align:middle line:84%
you basically look at
the goals and dreams

00:16:54.920 --> 00:16:56.837 align:middle line:84%
that you've set for
yourself, what you'll find

00:16:56.837 --> 00:16:59.810 align:middle line:84%
is often you're trying
to achieve something

00:16:59.810 --> 00:17:02.660 align:middle line:84%
because you want to get that
approval, that validation

00:17:02.660 --> 00:17:05.089 align:middle line:90%
from your dad, from your mother.

00:17:05.089 --> 00:17:06.710 align:middle line:84%
I have literally
worked with athletes

00:17:06.710 --> 00:17:09.140 align:middle line:84%
who have gone to the
pinnacle of their career--

00:17:09.140 --> 00:17:10.640 align:middle line:84%
they have gone to
the Olympics, they

00:17:10.640 --> 00:17:13.589 align:middle line:84%
have gone to the
World Cup soccer--

00:17:13.589 --> 00:17:17.050 align:middle line:84%
and their single motivation,
when you get to the core,

00:17:17.050 --> 00:17:20.069 align:middle line:84%
was they wanted their father,
in most cases-- some cases,

00:17:20.069 --> 00:17:20.869 align:middle line:90%
their mother--

00:17:20.869 --> 00:17:23.790 align:middle line:84%
to turn round and say,
I am proud of you.

00:17:23.790 --> 00:17:25.930 align:middle line:90%
I love you.

00:17:25.930 --> 00:17:28.460 align:middle line:84%
And they have spent
10 and 15 and 20

00:17:28.460 --> 00:17:33.390 align:middle line:84%
years trying to achieve
the pinnacle of this sport

00:17:33.390 --> 00:17:35.790 align:middle line:84%
for no other reason
than seeking validation

00:17:35.790 --> 00:17:38.460 align:middle line:84%
from the person that has
been close with them most

00:17:38.460 --> 00:17:40.470 align:middle line:90%
of their lives.

00:17:40.470 --> 00:17:43.220 align:middle line:84%
>> And I realized I was trying
to prove people wrong still,

00:17:43.220 --> 00:17:44.360 align:middle line:84%
and that's when I
shifted to saying,

00:17:44.360 --> 00:17:46.485 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to try to
prove people wrong anymore,

00:17:46.485 --> 00:17:49.490 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to try to lift others
up and prove people right

00:17:49.490 --> 00:17:51.980 align:middle line:84%
and live a life of
service and impact people.

00:17:51.980 --> 00:17:54.620 align:middle line:10%
And that's when I felt at
peace about my goal setting.

00:17:54.620 --> 00:17:58.170 align:middle line:90%


00:17:58.170 --> 00:18:01.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Michael Beckwith taught
me a model which is really

00:18:01.180 --> 00:18:01.980 align:middle line:90%
interesting.

00:18:01.980 --> 00:18:03.890 align:middle line:84%
It's called Kensho
versus Satori.

00:18:03.890 --> 00:18:08.210 align:middle line:84%
When you're living life moving
towards a particular purpose,

00:18:08.210 --> 00:18:10.820 align:middle line:84%
there are two very important
things to understand.

00:18:10.820 --> 00:18:14.810 align:middle line:84%
Life helps us grow
and correct and evolve

00:18:14.810 --> 00:18:18.530 align:middle line:84%
true Kensho, which
is growth by pain,

00:18:18.530 --> 00:18:21.650 align:middle line:84%
or Satori, which is
growth by insight.

00:18:21.650 --> 00:18:24.560 align:middle line:84%
Every now and then, you'll
have a Satori moment,

00:18:24.560 --> 00:18:27.260 align:middle line:84%
a sudden awakening, a eureka
moment, an insight that

00:18:27.260 --> 00:18:28.980 align:middle line:90%
helps you move forward.

00:18:28.980 --> 00:18:33.530 align:middle line:84%
But, for most people, that isn't
really going to be as easy.

00:18:33.530 --> 00:18:35.350 align:middle line:90%
Most of us grow true Kensho.

00:18:35.350 --> 00:18:37.490 align:middle line:90%
Kensho is growth from pain.

00:18:37.490 --> 00:18:39.170 align:middle line:84%
You fall sick and
end up hospitalized,

00:18:39.170 --> 00:18:42.710 align:middle line:84%
but you emerge with newfound
respect for your body

00:18:42.710 --> 00:18:44.660 align:middle line:84%
and making new
choices in how you're

00:18:44.660 --> 00:18:45.860 align:middle line:90%
going to treat your health.

00:18:45.860 --> 00:18:49.460 align:middle line:84%
You start a business, and
it fails, and it's painful,

00:18:49.460 --> 00:18:51.260 align:middle line:84%
but that's Kensho
because now you

00:18:51.260 --> 00:18:54.200 align:middle line:84%
know what not to do
in your next business.

00:18:54.200 --> 00:18:58.130 align:middle line:84%
A relationship dissolves, and
you experience heartbreak.

00:18:58.130 --> 00:18:59.930 align:middle line:84%
But that's Kensho
because now you

00:18:59.930 --> 00:19:02.450 align:middle line:84%
know the man or woman you
need to evolve to to create

00:19:02.450 --> 00:19:04.140 align:middle line:90%
even better relationships.

00:19:04.140 --> 00:19:06.940 align:middle line:84%
So when you see life
as Satori moment,

00:19:06.940 --> 00:19:10.790 align:middle line:84%
sudden awakenings, and
Kensho, growth through pain,

00:19:10.790 --> 00:19:13.610 align:middle line:84%
fear dissolves because
you know that even when

00:19:13.610 --> 00:19:16.070 align:middle line:84%
something bad happens
to you, it's simply

00:19:16.070 --> 00:19:20.180 align:middle line:84%
a friendly universe giving
you a lesson or fine tuning

00:19:20.180 --> 00:19:23.660 align:middle line:84%
and tweaking your direction
so you can get to your purpose

00:19:23.660 --> 00:19:25.330 align:middle line:90%
even faster.

00:19:25.330 --> 00:19:28.070 align:middle line:10%
>> When we have difficult times,
that difficulty can either

00:19:28.070 --> 00:19:31.640 align:middle line:10%
define us, it can diminish
us, or it can develop us.

00:19:31.640 --> 00:19:33.890 align:middle line:84%
We hear a lot about
post-traumatic stress,

00:19:33.890 --> 00:19:37.370 align:middle line:84%
but we don't hear a lot about
this other area of study

00:19:37.370 --> 00:19:39.050 align:middle line:90%
called post-traumatic growth.

00:19:39.050 --> 00:19:42.830 align:middle line:90%


00:19:42.830 --> 00:19:44.670 align:middle line:10%
This is where you come
through difficulty,

00:19:44.670 --> 00:19:47.320 align:middle line:10%
you come through adversity,
and on the other side,

00:19:47.320 --> 00:19:50.620 align:middle line:10%
you would never wish those
situations for anybody,

00:19:50.620 --> 00:19:52.900 align:middle line:10%
but you also wouldn't
change it for yourself,

