00:29:19.930 --> 00:29:23.380 align:middle line:84%
struggles, stress, depression,
because we're all going to face

00:29:23.380 --> 00:29:24.610 align:middle line:90%
challenges.

00:29:24.610 --> 00:29:26.710 align:middle line:84%
So what's the fuel
that's going to get us

00:29:26.710 --> 00:29:28.580 align:middle line:84%
through those
challenges of life?

00:29:28.580 --> 00:29:31.390 align:middle line:84%
And I think our
why and our vision

00:29:31.390 --> 00:29:33.130 align:middle line:90%
support us in having that fuel.

00:29:33.130 --> 00:29:44.110 align:middle line:90%


00:29:44.110 --> 00:29:46.330 align:middle line:90%
>> I grew up in a trailer--

00:29:46.330 --> 00:29:49.900 align:middle line:90%
my mom and dad, four kids.

00:29:49.900 --> 00:29:54.320 align:middle line:84%
We had a lot of canned food,
like hot dogs, smoked sausages.

00:29:54.320 --> 00:29:59.620 align:middle line:84%
I grew up on powdered milk
and all the processed food.

00:29:59.620 --> 00:30:02.710 align:middle line:84%
And I always felt, like,
a little bit left out,

00:30:02.710 --> 00:30:05.590 align:middle line:84%
a little bit different
because we didn't have much.

00:30:05.590 --> 00:30:08.440 align:middle line:84%
And the kids would make
fun of me and my clothes

00:30:08.440 --> 00:30:11.000 align:middle line:84%
and being skinny,
and just everything

00:30:11.000 --> 00:30:15.360 align:middle line:84%
was very much bullied
a lot at a young age.

00:30:15.360 --> 00:30:16.977 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't used to
being around people.

00:30:16.977 --> 00:30:19.060 align:middle line:84%
All I knew was I wanted
to get out of the country.

00:30:19.060 --> 00:30:21.730 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to be a
part of the in crowd.

00:30:21.730 --> 00:30:25.240 align:middle line:84%
I didn't want to be the country
girl with the Helping Hand

00:30:25.240 --> 00:30:27.940 align:middle line:84%
clothes and hair was
always messed up.

00:30:27.940 --> 00:30:31.240 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know what to do,
so I turned to sports.

00:30:31.240 --> 00:30:34.840 align:middle line:84%
And at first, I tried to
try out for cheerleading,

00:30:34.840 --> 00:30:36.310 align:middle line:90%
didn't make the team.

00:30:36.310 --> 00:30:37.435 align:middle line:90%
I tried out for basketball.

00:30:37.435 --> 00:30:38.920 align:middle line:10%
I was so clumsy.

00:30:38.920 --> 00:30:41.740 align:middle line:10%
I had a growth spurt, didn't
make the basketball team.

00:30:41.740 --> 00:30:45.850 align:middle line:84%
So I remember thinking
that, like, what can I do,

00:30:45.850 --> 00:30:50.110 align:middle line:84%
who do I have to be, because, as
I was, I didn't feel accepted.

00:30:50.110 --> 00:30:51.160 align:middle line:90%
I didn't feel loved.

00:30:51.160 --> 00:30:54.452 align:middle line:90%
And so I started to run.

00:30:54.452 --> 00:30:56.410 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I know, I
can get on the track team

00:30:56.410 --> 00:30:57.993 align:middle line:84%
because I would run
and catch the bus,

00:30:57.993 --> 00:31:00.190 align:middle line:84%
and I'd always get close
to beating my brothers,

00:31:00.190 --> 00:31:01.250 align:middle line:90%
and I was really fast.

00:31:01.250 --> 00:31:03.268 align:middle line:84%
So didn't make the
cheerleading team, didn't

00:31:03.268 --> 00:31:05.560 align:middle line:84%
make the basketball, so I
went out for track and field,

00:31:05.560 --> 00:31:07.090 align:middle line:84%
and I made the track
and field team.

00:31:07.090 --> 00:31:10.050 align:middle line:90%


00:31:10.050 --> 00:31:12.050 align:middle line:10%
When I started getting
on a track and field team

00:31:12.050 --> 00:31:15.470 align:middle line:10%
and getting these accolades
and getting faster and faster,

00:31:15.470 --> 00:31:17.460 align:middle line:10%
I found my sense of purpose.

00:31:17.460 --> 00:31:21.350 align:middle line:84%
It was like, oh, I'm important
because I can run fast,

00:31:21.350 --> 00:31:24.560 align:middle line:84%
and people are nice
to me, are kind to me.

00:31:24.560 --> 00:31:26.550 align:middle line:90%
My mom and dad cheer for me.

00:31:26.550 --> 00:31:30.950 align:middle line:84%
And so that was my first
feeling of being accepted.

00:31:30.950 --> 00:31:34.430 align:middle line:84%
When I went through
college my first year,

00:31:34.430 --> 00:31:35.780 align:middle line:90%
I was training so hard.

00:31:35.780 --> 00:31:37.410 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't getting enough sleep.

00:31:37.410 --> 00:31:40.670 align:middle line:10%
I graduated with a 3.8,
but all those studies

00:31:40.670 --> 00:31:42.470 align:middle line:10%
left me not getting
enough sleep,

00:31:42.470 --> 00:31:44.270 align:middle line:10%
not getting enough
recovery time.

00:31:44.270 --> 00:31:47.240 align:middle line:84%
We were supposed to get in the
cold whirlpool, rehab our body,

00:31:47.240 --> 00:31:48.910 align:middle line:84%
go swimming, things
to counterbalance

00:31:48.910 --> 00:31:50.660 align:middle line:84%
all the things we were
doing on the track,

00:31:50.660 --> 00:31:52.850 align:middle line:84%
and I would skip
those things to study.

00:31:52.850 --> 00:31:55.250 align:middle line:84%
And so eventually,
my sophomore year,

00:31:55.250 --> 00:31:57.650 align:middle line:84%
I got a stress fracture
in my lower back.

00:31:57.650 --> 00:31:59.420 align:middle line:84%
And it was the most
devastating thing

00:31:59.420 --> 00:32:00.560 align:middle line:84%
that had happened
to me because I

00:32:00.560 --> 00:32:02.520 align:middle line:84%
was slated to win the
conference the next year,

00:32:02.520 --> 00:32:05.090 align:middle line:84%
and all of a sudden, my
coach was like, I'm sorry,

00:32:05.090 --> 00:32:06.620 align:middle line:90%
you're out for the season.

00:32:06.620 --> 00:32:08.360 align:middle line:90%
And I'm just, like--

00:32:08.360 --> 00:32:10.010 align:middle line:90%
it was just in shock.

00:32:10.010 --> 00:32:12.380 align:middle line:84%
I didn't believe it,
and I got really sad.

00:32:12.380 --> 00:32:14.280 align:middle line:84%
I was crying in
classes, and my teachers

00:32:14.280 --> 00:32:15.770 align:middle line:90%
sent me to the counselor.

00:32:15.770 --> 00:32:17.520 align:middle line:84%
And the counselor was
like, you know what,

00:32:17.520 --> 00:32:18.830 align:middle line:90%
I think you should try yoga.

00:32:18.830 --> 00:32:22.070 align:middle line:84%
And at the time, I didn't
know what yoga was.

00:32:22.070 --> 00:32:24.650 align:middle line:84%
I just thought yoga
was Buddha, and it

00:32:24.650 --> 00:32:27.960 align:middle line:84%
was separate from Christianity,
and I couldn't do it.

00:32:27.960 --> 00:32:30.987 align:middle line:84%
But she was like, no,
it's just stretching.

00:32:30.987 --> 00:32:32.820 align:middle line:84%
I was like, OK, well,
I don't have a choice.

00:32:32.820 --> 00:32:33.903 align:middle line:90%
I got kicked out of class.

00:32:33.903 --> 00:32:36.117 align:middle line:84%
I gotta go do this
yoga stretching thing.

00:32:36.117 --> 00:32:37.700 align:middle line:84%
And so I went to
class, and I remember

00:32:37.700 --> 00:32:39.230 align:middle line:84%
trying to do a
Headstand, and I felt

00:32:39.230 --> 00:32:42.125 align:middle line:84%
like my brain was going to
ooze out the top of my skull.

00:32:42.125 --> 00:32:44.210 align:middle line:84%
I was just like, I
am not made for this.

00:32:44.210 --> 00:32:47.005 align:middle line:84%
This is painful,
and this is not me.

00:32:47.005 --> 00:32:48.880 align:middle line:84%
And I remember my teacher
seeing me struggle.

00:32:48.880 --> 00:32:50.210 align:middle line:84%
She came up to me,
and she looked at me,

00:32:50.210 --> 00:32:52.085 align:middle line:84%
and she was like, I just
want you to breathe.

00:32:52.085 --> 00:32:56.010 align:middle line:84%
I took a big inhale with
her, and we exhaled together,

00:32:56.010 --> 00:32:57.890 align:middle line:84%
and for that moment,
I felt spirit.

00:32:57.890 --> 00:33:01.240 align:middle line:90%


00:33:01.240 --> 00:33:04.380 align:middle line:84%
Then eventually, after a
year of swimming and biking

00:33:04.380 --> 00:33:06.900 align:middle line:84%
and meditation and
yoga, I came back

00:33:06.900 --> 00:33:09.210 align:middle line:84%
to win the conference
meet in college,

00:33:09.210 --> 00:33:12.600 align:middle line:84%
and I led Wichita State to its
first women's championship.

00:33:12.600 --> 00:33:14.290 align:middle line:90%
And it was because of yoga.

00:33:14.290 --> 00:33:17.670 align:middle line:84%
And so, of course, I
was like, yay, win.

00:33:17.670 --> 00:33:19.622 align:middle line:84%
So I moved to
California to train

00:33:19.622 --> 00:33:22.080 align:middle line:84%
in San Diego, which is close
to the Olympic Training Center

00:33:22.080 --> 00:33:23.670 align:middle line:90%
because if I'm so close--

00:33:23.670 --> 00:33:24.677 align:middle line:90%
I've only had one year.

00:33:24.677 --> 00:33:26.260 align:middle line:84%
If I could do all
of that in one year,

00:33:26.260 --> 00:33:28.510 align:middle line:84%
what can I do if I had a
really great coach and really

00:33:28.510 --> 00:33:29.730 align:middle line:90%
great training?

00:33:29.730 --> 00:33:31.283 align:middle line:90%
And I came out here and I did.

00:33:31.283 --> 00:33:32.700 align:middle line:84%
Every time I stepped
on the track,

00:33:32.700 --> 00:33:34.158 align:middle line:84%
I got better and
better and better.

00:33:34.158 --> 00:33:37.360 align:middle line:84%
But, again, I wasn't
taking care of myself.

00:33:37.360 --> 00:33:40.110 align:middle line:84%
I became a personal
trainer at 24 Hour Fitness.

00:33:40.110 --> 00:33:42.900 align:middle line:84%
I was working from
5:00 AM to 10:00,

00:33:42.900 --> 00:33:45.810 align:middle line:84%
and then I'd run track
from 11:00 to about 3:00,

00:33:45.810 --> 00:33:49.220 align:middle line:84%
and then I would go back and
work from 5:00 to 10:00 again.

00:33:49.220 --> 00:33:51.630 align:middle line:84%
I had a full list of clients,
getting great results

00:33:51.630 --> 00:33:53.297 align:middle line:84%
with them, but I was
getting very little

00:33:53.297 --> 00:33:55.380 align:middle line:84%
sleep and, of course,
very little recovery.

00:33:55.380 --> 00:33:56.640 align:middle line:90%
So what happens?

00:33:56.640 --> 00:33:58.980 align:middle line:84%
Injured again-- this time,
I pulled my hamstring.

00:33:58.980 --> 00:34:02.970 align:middle line:84%
So here I am, injured again,
and so where do I turn--

00:34:02.970 --> 00:34:04.500 align:middle line:90%
yoga, meditation.

00:34:04.500 --> 00:34:07.035 align:middle line:84%
This time, it healed me
again, and this time, I

00:34:07.035 --> 00:34:09.480 align:middle line:84%
was like, you know what,
there's something to this.

00:34:09.480 --> 00:34:10.920 align:middle line:90%
This is amazing.

00:34:10.920 --> 00:34:13.679 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, you know what,
I can't let this go again.

00:34:13.679 --> 00:34:16.132 align:middle line:84%
I need to commit to
this as a lifestyle

00:34:16.132 --> 00:34:17.590 align:middle line:84%
and not just come
in and out of it.

00:34:17.590 --> 00:34:20.040 align:middle line:84%
So I decided to sign up
for my first yoga teacher

00:34:20.040 --> 00:34:22.260 align:middle line:84%
training and not just any
yoga teacher training.

00:34:22.260 --> 00:34:25.050 align:middle line:84%
I signed up for Ashtanga,
which is the hardest

00:34:25.050 --> 00:34:27.540 align:middle line:90%
form of yoga you possibly do.

00:34:27.540 --> 00:34:32.449 align:middle line:84%
And in that 30 days, I
completely changed my life.

00:34:32.449 --> 00:34:34.290 align:middle line:90%
I had visions.

00:34:34.290 --> 00:34:35.940 align:middle line:90%
I felt so connected.

00:34:35.940 --> 00:34:36.870 align:middle line:90%
I saw my purpose.

00:34:36.870 --> 00:34:39.010 align:middle line:84%
I saw me making a difference
in people's lives.

00:34:39.010 --> 00:34:39.870 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know how.

00:34:39.870 --> 00:34:42.590 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know I would be
doing what I'm doing today,

00:34:42.590 --> 00:34:45.090 align:middle line:84%
but I knew that I was going to
be doing something great just

00:34:45.090 --> 00:34:48.120 align:middle line:90%
using my life and my voice.

00:34:48.120 --> 00:34:51.335 align:middle line:84%
And in that moment, I made a
commitment to do yoga daily.

00:34:51.335 --> 00:35:04.080 align:middle line:90%


00:35:04.080 --> 00:35:05.910 align:middle line:84%
>> The last time I
checked, which was 2015,

00:35:05.910 --> 00:35:10.020 align:middle line:84%
there were 1,400 different
studies on the power

00:35:10.020 --> 00:35:13.950 align:middle line:84%
of meditation, everything
from helping reduce the onset

00:35:13.950 --> 00:35:17.220 align:middle line:84%
of heart disease to helping
improve your skin to improving

00:35:17.220 --> 00:35:21.430 align:middle line:84%
productivity to improving
compassion and empathy.

00:35:21.430 --> 00:35:25.080 align:middle line:84%
So meditation is one
of those powerful tools

00:35:25.080 --> 00:35:28.050 align:middle line:84%
that any human being can
bring in their life to improve

00:35:28.050 --> 00:35:29.580 align:middle line:90%
their functioning in the world.

00:35:29.580 --> 00:35:31.890 align:middle line:84%
The thing is, we don't
know why meditation works.

00:35:31.890 --> 00:35:36.330 align:middle line:84%
Nobody has yet figured
out the exact reasons

00:35:36.330 --> 00:35:38.275 align:middle line:84%
why meditation causes
all of these feelings.

00:35:38.275 --> 00:35:40.650 align:middle line:84%
There are theories, but no
one has really boiled it down.

00:35:40.650 --> 00:35:43.950 align:middle line:84%
But just because we
don't know why it works

00:35:43.950 --> 00:35:45.600 align:middle line:90%
doesn't mean we can't use it.

00:35:45.600 --> 00:35:47.880 align:middle line:84%
I mean, for the longest
time, human beings

00:35:47.880 --> 00:35:50.460 align:middle line:90%
had no idea what the sun was.

00:35:50.460 --> 00:35:53.640 align:middle line:84%
Ancient cultures thought it
was a god or a giant fireball,

00:35:53.640 --> 00:35:56.560 align:middle line:84%
but we could still use
the sun for agriculture,

00:35:56.560 --> 00:35:59.700 align:middle line:84%
for navigation, for warmth,
for direction, for heat.

00:35:59.700 --> 00:36:02.550 align:middle line:84%
And likewise, we don't
know why meditation works,

00:36:02.550 --> 00:36:07.410 align:middle line:84%
but 1,400 studies have now shown
that meditation pretty much

00:36:07.410 --> 00:36:11.610 align:middle line:84%
enhances so many multiple
dimensions of human living

00:36:11.610 --> 00:36:13.590 align:middle line:84%
that every single
human being should

00:36:13.590 --> 00:36:16.140 align:middle line:84%
be making this part of
their daily practice.

00:36:16.140 --> 00:36:19.520 align:middle line:84%
>> I know so many people that
meditate from sports stars

00:36:19.520 --> 00:36:21.060 align:middle line:84%
to high performers
on every level,

00:36:21.060 --> 00:36:24.010 align:middle line:84%
and everyone has their own
flavor and their own style.

00:36:24.010 --> 00:36:26.640 align:middle line:84%
Some people it's a
form of visualization,

00:36:26.640 --> 00:36:29.220 align:middle line:84%
and some people it's just
a form of concentration.

00:36:29.220 --> 00:36:31.990 align:middle line:84%
>> Everyone has to find
their own practice.

00:36:31.990 --> 00:36:34.380 align:middle line:84%
But what we know,
without any doubt,

00:36:34.380 --> 00:36:37.710 align:middle line:84%
is that all of the science of
both mindfulness and meditation

00:36:37.710 --> 00:36:39.240 align:middle line:84%
is proving over
and over again, we

00:36:39.240 --> 00:36:43.170 align:middle line:84%
can decrease our stress
by will, by going

00:36:43.170 --> 00:36:45.480 align:middle line:84%
into a meditative
state we can improve

00:36:45.480 --> 00:36:50.010 align:middle line:84%
our overall health by will by
going into a meditative state.

00:36:50.010 --> 00:36:54.100 align:middle line:84%
We can improve our daily
productivity, our creativity,

00:36:54.100 --> 00:36:56.400 align:middle line:84%
our resilience,
our relationships.

00:36:56.400 --> 00:36:58.620 align:middle line:84%
Every facet of our life we
can improve by meditation,

00:36:58.620 --> 00:37:00.078 align:middle line:84%
but meditation
doesn't just happen.

00:37:00.078 --> 00:37:03.540 align:middle line:84%
You have to take the
time and go in that.

00:37:03.540 --> 00:37:04.386 align:middle line:90%
Place.

00:37:04.386 --> 00:37:07.075 align:middle line:10%
>> So there's tools out there,
but the first step is to really

00:37:07.075 --> 00:37:09.450 align:middle line:10%
give yourself permission to
slow down and giving yourself

00:37:09.450 --> 00:37:10.980 align:middle line:10%
permission to do nothing.

00:37:10.980 --> 00:37:13.530 align:middle line:10%
And that nothingness can come
on your meditation pillow,

00:37:13.530 --> 00:37:15.900 align:middle line:10%
or that nothingness can come
even if you give yourself

00:37:15.900 --> 00:37:18.990 align:middle line:10%
five minutes in the morning
to sit with your tea

00:37:18.990 --> 00:37:22.980 align:middle line:10%
and look out the window with
no device near you at all,

00:37:22.980 --> 00:37:26.580 align:middle line:10%
with no to-do list in your
mind, but to do nothing.

00:37:26.580 --> 00:37:28.590 align:middle line:84%
>> I do it when
I'm in a taxicab.

00:37:28.590 --> 00:37:30.150 align:middle line:84%
